      "catalysts_full": {
        "path": "wiki/tickers/AMD/catalysts.md",
        "mode": "full",
        "content": "# AMD \u2014 Catalysts\n\n## TL;DR\n\nThe next binary event is Q1 2026 earnings on May 5, 2026 after market close. The structural bull catalysts \u2014 the $60B Meta infrastructure deal and AMD's first-mover position on TSMC 2nm \u2014 are already reflected in price following the parabolic April run. The structural bear catalyst \u2014 25% tariff on advanced AI chips \u2014 is an ongoing margin headwind not yet fully digested. Earnings on May 5 is the resolution event.\n\n## Upcoming events\n\n| Date | Event | Expected impact |\n|---|---|---|\n| May 5, 2026 (after close) | Q1 2026 earnings | Binary \u2014 consensus EPS $1.18, revenue ~$9.8B (+32% YoY) |\n| 2H 2026 | MI450 GPU launch | Positive if benchmarks beat H200; neutral if delayed |\n| 2H 2026 | Helios rack-scale platform launch | Positive \u2014 positions AMD for multi-GPU hyperscale deals |\n| Ongoing | TSMC tariff exemption decision | Potential positive relief if hyperscaler exemptions pass |\n\nSources: web_research/AMD.json runs 20260415_110848 and swing_20260411_211655.\n\n## Recent news synthesis\n\n**Positive:**\n- **Meta $60B infrastructure deal** \u2014 Multi-year commitment covering AMD GPUs, Venice-architecture CPUs, and custom silicon co-engineering. Described by analysts as transformational for AMD's Data Center revenue visibility (source: web_research/AMD.json, run 20260415_110848, Capital.com/Motley Fool, April 2026).\n- **TSMC 2nm first adopter** \u2014 CEO Lisa Su confirmed April 15, 2026 that AMD will be first on TSMC's 2nm node. Ahead of both Nvidia and Intel on next process generation (source: web_research/AMD.json, run 20260415_110848).\n- **Q4 2025 beat** \u2014 Revenue $10.27B (+34% YoY), Data Center $5.38B record, EPS $1.53 vs $1.24 estimate. Shares fell on soft Q1 sequential guidance despite the beat (source: web_research/AMD.json, run 20260415_110848).\n- **AMD server CPU share crosses 40%** \u2014 Pricing power at Intel's expense, validated by multiple analyst reports (source: web_research/AMD.json, run swing_20260411_211655).\n- **Goldman Sachs top pick** heading into Q1 earnings season; Erste Group upgraded to Buy (source: web_research/AMD.json, run swing_20260411_211655).\n\n**Negative:**\n- **25% tariff on advanced AI chips** \u2014 Enacted January 14, 2026, covers AMD MI325X and Nvidia H200. Raising GPU/memory prices, compressing margins on hyperscaler deals (source: web_research/AMD.json, run 20260415_110848, Axios/CNN Business).\n- **Nvidia market share gap widened** \u2014 Nvidia holds ~89% server GPU share despite MI-series ramp. AMD's addressable market is smaller than the headline AI tailwind implies (source: web_research/AMD.json, run 20260415_110848, IDC/April 2026).\n\n## Insider activity\n\nCEO Lisa Su sold approximately $16 million in shares in March 2026. Insider distribution tracked at 83 buys / 188 sells \u2014 sellers outnumber buyers at the board level by more than 2:1 (source: swing_head_trader signal, run swing_20260411_211655). This is an ongoing overhang but has not historically been a short-term directional catalyst.\n\n## Analyst consensus\n\n- **Rating:** Buy (consensus across all three runs)\n- **Avg price target:** $274\u2013$277 (April 2026); median $290; range $120\u2013$380\n- **Bull target:** Evercore ISI $358, Melius Research $380\n- **Coverage:** 39 Buy / 0 Sell among 51 analysts as of April 2026\n- **Full-year EPS growth:** ~72% consensus for 2026, ~60% for 2027\n\nSources: web_research/AMD.json, runs 20260415_110848 and swing_20260411_211655.\n",
